e values, refer to ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSCheckbox","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"type":"heading","text":"Particular cases","level":2,"anchor":"Particular-cases"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"An "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSCheckboxIndeterminate","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" can be related to an error situation, for example troubles for a formular."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"A dedicated look-and-feel is implemented for that if the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"isError"},{"type":"text","text":" flag is risen."}]},{"text":"Accessibility considerations","type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"Accessibility-considerations"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Note also the component must be instanciated with a string parameter used as accessibility label."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"It is a good pratice (at least) to define a label for a component without text for accessibility reasons. This label will be vocalized by "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Voice Over"}]},{"type":"text","text":"."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"The vocalization tool will also use, after the label, a description of the component (if disabled, if error context), and a fake trait for checkbox."}]},{"type":"heading","text":"Cases forbidden by design","level":2,"anchor":"Cases-forbidden-by-design"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The design system does not allow to have both an error situation and a disabled component.","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"}]},{"text":"Code samples","type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"Code-samples"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["    \/\/ Supposing we have an indeterminate state checkbox","   